author: @BerkayCelik
text: In order to solve the problem, pip, an alternative to setuptools/easy_install, provides an "uninstall" command. So if you already have the wrong module installed, use "pip uninstall modulename_64bit" and then you can run "pip install modulename_32bit" or vice versa.
